{"kind": "page", "url": "https://code.claude.com/docs/en/zero-data-retention.md", "path": "en/zero-data-retention.md", "title": "Zero data retention", "description": "Learn about Zero Data Retention (ZDR) for Claude Code on Claude for Enterprise, including scope, disabled features, and how to request enablement.", "description_source": "llms.txt", "content_hash": "8054c514c8ebfdc9ea047f52efbd1973ab3a836912e7052fa32124c1519f00c2", "volatile": false}
{"kind": "section", "id": "https://code.claude.com/docs/en/zero-data-retention.md#overview", "page_url": "https://code.claude.com/docs/en/zero-data-retention.md", "anchor": "overview", "breadcrumb": "Zero data retention > Overview", "level": 2, "position": 0, "text": "> Learn about Zero Data Retention (ZDR) for Claude Code on Claude for Enterprise, including scope, disabled features, and how to request enablement.\n\nZero Data Retention (ZDR) is available for Claude Code when used through Claude for Enterprise. When ZDR is enabled, prompts and model responses generated during Claude Code sessions are processed in real time and not stored by Anthropic after the response is returned, except where needed to comply with law or combat misuse.\n\nZDR on Claude for Enterprise gives enterprise customers the ability to use Claude Code with zero data retention and access administrative capabilities:\n\n- Cost controls per user\n- Analytics dashboard\n- Server-managed settings\n- Audit logs\n\nZDR for Claude Code on Claude for Enterprise applies only to Anthropic's direct platform. For Claude deployments on AWS Bedrock, Google Vertex AI, or Microsoft Foundry, refer to those platforms' data retention policies.", "synthesized": false, "parent_section_id": null, "external_links": []}
{"kind": "callout", "id": "45d7ba787a79d76b", "section_id": "https://code.claude.com/docs/en/zero-data-retention.md#zdr-scope", "position": 0, "callout_kind": "warning", "text": "ZDR is enabled on a per-organization basis. Each new organization requires ZDR to be enabled separately by your Anthropic account team. ZDR does not automatically apply to new organizations created under the same account. Contact your account team to enable ZDR for any new organizations."}
{"kind": "section", "id": "https://code.claude.com/docs/en/zero-data-retention.md#what-zdr-covers", "page_url": "https://code.claude.com/docs/en/zero-data-retention.md", "anchor": "what-zdr-covers", "breadcrumb": "Zero data retention > ZDR scope > What ZDR covers", "level": 3, "position": 2, "text": "ZDR covers model inference calls made through Claude Code on Claude for Enterprise. When you use Claude Code in your terminal, the prompts you send and the responses Claude generates are not retained by Anthropic. This applies regardless of which Claude model is used.", "synthesized": false, "parent_section_id": "https://code.claude.com/docs/en/zero-data-retention.md#zdr-scope", "external_links": []}
{"kind": "tablerow", "id": "336a44b1b86f12ff", "section_id": "https://code.claude.com/docs/en/zero-data-retention.md#what-zdr-does-not-cover", "position": 0, "table_position": 0, "headers": ["feature", "details"], "cells": ["Chat on claude.ai", "Chat conversations through the Claude for Enterprise web interface are not covered by ZDR."]}
{"kind": "tablerow", "id": "e11a0889333eb75c", "section_id": "https://code.claude.com/docs/en/zero-data-retention.md#what-zdr-does-not-cover", "position": 1, "table_position": 0, "headers": ["feature", "details"], "cells": ["Cowork", "Cowork sessions are not covered by ZDR."]}
{"kind": "tablerow", "id": "fcb8abad0a396a42", "section_id": "https://code.claude.com/docs/en/zero-data-retention.md#what-zdr-does-not-cover", "position": 2, "table_position": 0, "headers": ["feature", "details"], "cells": ["Claude Code Analytics", "Does not store prompts or model responses, but collects productivity metadata such as account emails and usage statistics. Contribution metrics are not available for ZDR organizations; the analytics dashboard shows usage metrics only."]}
{"kind": "tablerow", "id": "c8b85af193cfa1e4", "section_id": "https://code.claude.com/docs/en/zero-data-retention.md#what-zdr-does-not-cover", "position": 3, "table_position": 0, "headers": ["feature", "details"], "cells": ["User and seat management", "Administrative data such as account emails and seat assignments is retained under standard policies."]}
{"kind": "tablerow", "id": "40ef272f6fd8fd49", "section_id": "https://code.claude.com/docs/en/zero-data-retention.md#what-zdr-does-not-cover", "position": 4, "table_position": 0, "headers": ["feature", "details"], "cells": ["Third-party integrations", "Data processed by third-party tools, MCP servers, or other external integrations is not covered by ZDR. Review those services' data handling practices independently."]}
{"kind": "section", "id": "https://code.claude.com/docs/en/zero-data-retention.md#what-zdr-does-not-cover", "page_url": "https://code.claude.com/docs/en/zero-data-retention.md", "anchor": "what-zdr-does-not-cover", "breadcrumb": "Zero data retention > ZDR scope > What ZDR does not cover", "level": 3, "position": 3, "text": "ZDR does not extend to the following, even for organizations with ZDR enabled. These features follow standard data retention policies:", "synthesized": false, "parent_section_id": "https://code.claude.com/docs/en/zero-data-retention.md#zdr-scope", "external_links": ["http://claude.ai"]}
