{"kind": "tablerow", "id": "72cb878fc394633b", "section_id": "https://code.claude.com/docs/en/zero-data-retention.md#features-disabled-under-zdr", "position": 1, "table_position": 0, "headers": ["feature", "reason"], "cells": ["Remote sessions from the Desktop app", "Requires persistent session data that includes prompts and completions."]}
{"kind": "tablerow", "id": "c4bd211c6b6b2347", "section_id": "https://code.claude.com/docs/en/zero-data-retention.md#features-disabled-under-zdr", "position": 2, "table_position": 0, "headers": ["feature", "reason"], "cells": ["Feedback submission (`/feedback`)", "Submitting feedback sends conversation data to Anthropic."]}
{"kind": "section", "id": "https://code.claude.com/docs/en/zero-data-retention.md#features-disabled-under-zdr", "page_url": "https://code.claude.com/docs/en/zero-data-retention.md", "anchor": "features-disabled-under-zdr", "breadcrumb": "Zero data retention > Features disabled under ZDR", "level": 2, "position": 4, "text": "When ZDR is enabled for a Claude Code organization on Claude for Enterprise, certain features that require storing prompts or completions are automatically disabled at the backend level:\n\nThese features are blocked in the backend regardless of client-side display. If you see a disabled feature in the Claude Code terminal during startup, attempting to use it returns an error indicating the organization's policies do not allow that action.\n\nFuture features may also be disabled if they require storing prompts or completions.", "synthesized": false, "parent_section_id": null, "external_links": []}
{"kind": "section", "id": "https://code.claude.com/docs/en/zero-data-retention.md#data-retention-for-policy-violations", "page_url": "https://code.claude.com/docs/en/zero-data-retention.md", "anchor": "data-retention-for-policy-violations", "breadcrumb": "Zero data retention > Data retention for policy violations", "level": 2, "position": 5, "text": "Even with ZDR enabled, Anthropic may retain data where required by law or to address Usage Policy violations. If a session is flagged for a policy violation, Anthropic may retain the associated inputs and outputs for up to 2 years, consistent with Anthropic's standard ZDR policy.", "synthesized": false, "parent_section_id": null, "external_links": []}
{"kind": "section", "id": "https://code.claude.com/docs/en/zero-data-retention.md#request-zdr", "page_url": "https://code.claude.com/docs/en/zero-data-retention.md", "anchor": "request-zdr", "breadcrumb": "Zero data retention > Request ZDR", "level": 2, "position": 6, "text": "To request ZDR for Claude Code on Claude for Enterprise, contact sales or your Anthropic account team. Your account team will submit the request internally, and Anthropic will review and enable ZDR on your organization after confirming eligibility. All enablement actions are audit-logged.\n\nIf you are currently using ZDR for Claude Code via pay-as-you-go API keys, you can transition to Claude for Enterprise to gain access to administrative features while maintaining ZDR for Claude Code. Contact your account team to coordinate the migration.", "synthesized": false, "parent_section_id": null, "external_links": ["https://www.anthropic.com/contact-sales?utm_source=claude_code&utm_medium=docs&utm_content=zero_data_retention_request"]}
